profileData.title: Broker Associate
profileData.bio:
Robert has been helping buyers and sellers with their residential real estate transactions since 1990 in the Denver Metro area.

Robert is knowledgeable and reliable, providing top notch real estate expertise for his clients.

Robert specializes in representing buyers and sellers of single family homes, condos and town homes, 2-4 unit investment properties, and dealing with new home builders.

Make a great move and call Robert for all of your real estate needs!

profileData.profile_description: default agent role for Jonathan Bich
profileData.title: Broker
profileData.bio:
I was born west of Spokane in the beautiful valley of Wenatchee, Washington to a mother and father who believed that hard work and dedication would always be the keys to success.  After graduating from Wenatchee High School, I entered the Air Force in the summer of 1981 to experience the world, and wound up making it a career for over 20 years.  Along the way I met a captivating southern girl named Regina, and married her immediately.  She has been my wife now for 35 years.  Together we have three great boys:  Justin, is our oldest and served in the Marine Corp with the 2nd LAR H&S Company and who also survived 2 tours in Iraq.  He has two beautiful little girls.  Brandon, my second, is my right-hand man and works with me every day helping good people with their real estate needs. He is married to his high school sweetheart and also served as a percussionist for the United States Army Band stationed at Fort Drum New York and is now part of the National Guard and has a little boy and a new little girl; and Jesse our youngest, also married and lives and works right here in Spokane too!

In the Air Force I held many positions, but my professional background was in the telecommunications field.  As a Branch Manager I was responsible for the maintenance and configuration of all telecommunications media systems on an installation.  One of the many daily aspects of my job was acting as chief liaison for all new requirements.  I provided technical expertise to reduce scheduling conflicts, resolve critical issues, and facilitate on-time implementation of many high dollar projects. You will find these skills crucial to your home buying or selling process.  

Military life meant moving a lot, and over the years I moved my family an average of every 23 months.  This provided me with a unique background in understanding exactly what to look for in a professional Realtor and helped develop an ability to quickly analyze the housing market and find the best home value in a short amount of time and this ability I will pass on to you!
	
This background has also become extremely useful in the difficult and always emotional task of buying or selling a home, and then preparing for the move.  I have become a specialist on the aspects of relocation, so when the time comes, I can be there to assist with your move whether it’s across town or across the nation.

In summary, I have been helping people to buy and sell their homes now for over 17 years and I take my career very seriously.  I feel it is this professionalism, knowledge, and appreciation for the Real Estate industry that I can personally offer you.  Whatever your needs, our company, and especially Brandon and myself, will go to great lengths making sure you are completely satisfied.

profileData.profile_description: default agent role for Cathy Dernbach
profileData.title: Broker
profileData.bio:
Hello, my name is Cathy Dernbach. I have been a Realtor in the state of Washington in the greater Spokane Area since 1985. I was born and raised in Tacoma, Washington. After attending Gonzaga University here in Spokane, I lived in Portland, Oregon and the Vancouver area for about 13 years. Then, I returned to Spokane and have resided here ever since.

My hobbies include kayaking, snowshoeing, cross country skiing, canoeing, hiking, biking, tennis, and racquetball. I spend my free time exploring the great outdoors. We are blessed to live in the Pacific Northwest. There are so many activities to choose from especially here in Spokane. 

I ventured into real estate by chance and here I am 30 years later. It is my professionalism, knowledge, and genuine love of the Real Estate Industry that I have to offer you.

I feel fortunate to make my living doing a job I love. I meet so many wonderful and genuine people while helping them find a place to call home or helping them find an investment for their future. Whatever your need might be, I will go to the great lengths to make sure that you are satisfied. The next time that you require Real Estate assistance, whether you are purchasing or selling any property in the Spokane area, please give me a call. Make use of the benefits my company and I have to offer you.

office.name: Windermere Real Estate/City Group
office.slogan: Feel at Home with Our Agents

feedbackData.comment: We have done three transactions with Cathy over the past four years (two purchases and a sale).  All three have gone exceedingly smoothly due to her knowledge of the market and her wealth of experience in the real estate business.  She communicates well with everyone concerned in transactions and we always felt up to date on what was going on.  We would highly recommend Cathy to anyone buying or selling a property.

office.name: CENTURY 21 Beutler & Associates
office.slogan: Global reach, local knowledge

profileData.title: true
profileData.bio: I was born and raised in Spokane Washington and find joy in exposing others to all of the great things this town has to offer. I couldn't wait to get out and see the world once I graduated from Shadle Park High School. Travelling the globe, I learned that Spokane was the place where I wanted to settle down. While working my first job as a pipe fitter here, I learned what it is to work and work hard. This ethic has followed me throughout my entire career and has served myself and others well. One of my favorite jobs was working on a ranch in Montana whose sole purpose was to provide a life-long home for adults with special needs. This experience was one of the most fulfilling of my life and taught me the true meaning of service and the value of relationships. Eventually I settled in Spokane and am happily married to the love of my life. My passion is recreating in the wilderness with friends and family and, of course, the dog. Most of the time you can find me in my backyard gardening, playing lawn games or practicing my chipping and putting skills. My journey eventually led me to real estate where I am able combine my knowledge of the area, work ethic, and commitment to service which my clients appreciate most.
profileData.areas_served: Spokane County

profileData.profile_description: default agent role for Kolby Schoenrock
profileData.title: Agent
profileData.bio:
My goal as a Real Estate Agent is to love and serve my clients in finding them the perfect home to meet their needs. 

I started me career in Real Estate as a Residential Appraiser in 2012. As a residential appraiser, I average over 250 appraisals per year and I have become an expert in valuing real estate. This experience gives me the upper hand in knowing current market value and ensuring my clients are ahead of the competition. I want every person who I get the opportunity to serve to have piece of mind knowing I will not only work hard for them but also make sure they are well aware of the market value for any property. This leads to buyers always buying at or below market value and sellers pricing their homes at the optimal price for a quick sale without leaving money on the table. 

With my expertise in valuing residential property, many of my clients are people looking for homes with potential for future equity! In the Spokane County market, there are lots of homes with incredible opportunity for individuals looking to fix-in quick equity. I love to use my expertise in helping my clients find these houses!

Please give me a call if you have any real estate questions, I would love to do my best to help!
specialties: Knowing/Finding True Market Value for Residential

office.name: Windermere Real Estate/City Group
office.slogan: Feel at Home with Our Agents

feedbackData.comment: Kolby is a wonderful agent to work with. Our family recently moved to Spokane from California and Kolby was amazing at guiding us through the process. He was patient with us as we learned the different areas of Spokane, due in large part to his guidance! He was also so helpful in showing us a variety of homes so that we could hone in on the things that are most important to us in  choosing a home. We've worked with Kolby for several months and the entire time we have been impressed with his knowledge, professionalism, and kindness. We never felt rushed and always felt supported throughout the entire process of buying our new family home. We are very grateful to have worked with him and will definitely do so again in the future!

It was truly a pleasure working with Kolby to find our new home in Spokane!  Kolby quickly narrowed our search down to exactly what we truly needed in a home and showed us several neighborhoods that would qualify.  He helped us choose the right home that was perfect for the family and helped us with schools, and even helped us save half a point on our mortgage by referring us to a great lender. He gave excellent advice when we got into a short bidding war on the home of our dreams and helped us secure the home. Kolby is highly knowledgeable and very patient and helped us learn about a market we knew nothing about.  I would HIGHLY RECOMMEND Kolby to anyone looking for an OUTSTANDING realtor!

Kolby provided an impeccable service! Not only was he extremely helpful in finding the perfect house, he navigated the negotiating process absolutely flawlessly. I consider myself to be great at making deals as I have 15 years of sales experience and thrive on it, but Kolby has an uncanny ability to analyze every aspect of the home, market, and the buyer to truly find the best settling point in order to maximize your hard earned dollars. I wouldn't hesitate for a moment to, again, put my full trust in Kolby. He is likely one of the most honest people out there! I gave him nearly an impossible task with my real estate request and he pulled every string you could think of to make it happen. I owe him my gratitude for being in the home I am currently in. When I expand my real estate portfolio for investment purposes, he will undoubtedly be the first person I inquire with.
Kolby made the process very easy and enjoyable for me. He's the best!

profileData.profile_description: default agent role for Molly Cline
profileData.title: Broker
profileData.bio:
Buying and selling real estate is, for most of us, one of life's big steps - it can be a tension-filled and emotionally demanding event. I'll navigate you through the process of buying and selling with diligence and care. I understand how essential it is to listen and learn what is most important to you, and ensure that your needs are met. My years of experience in real estate transactions, project management, event coordination and customer service will serve you well; I know how to pay attention to the details, and have high level achievement awards to back that claim. I'll help you achieve your goals with efficiency and professionalism.
A Yank by birth, I was born and raised in the Northeast. After living in Boston, Massachusetts, and Southern California, my husband, Winfield, and I migrated to the Inland Northwest in 1999, and have loved living here ever since! We enjoy all that Spokane has to offer - warm, friendly people, four distinct seasons, excellent snowboarding and hiking, beautiful lakes, great schools, colleges, music, art and culture - too many things to list. Winfield and I are delighted to live in Spokane and feel lucky to have raised our two boys here, in the Northwest`s best!

If the home is where the heart is, then it is definitely a place to be treated with great care. Whether you are thinking of buying a new home, or ready to sell your home, or you know someone who is doing either of those and needs a realtor, I am able to help through the process, providing a gratifying and successful experience.

Born and raised in Spokane, having written extensively about the city during my 12 years as editor-in-chief of Spokane Coeur d’Alene Living, the city magazine, and having literally written the book on Spokane (Spokane’s Stories: 28 Stories of the People, Places and Events That Have Shaped Spokane), I know this city and its neighborhoods.

profileData.profile_description: default agent for Tony Higley
profileData.title: Agent
profileData.bio:
ith over 40 years of professional experience managing real estate, investments and assets; fundraising, strategic business planning and leadership, Tony J. Higley’s career has stretched from residential realtor, to certified appraiser, small business owner, and executive director of a multimillion dollar non-profit foundation.

As a lifetime resident of Spokane, Higley has been deeply committed to the community, and to helping those in the area achieve their greatest potential. When he graduated from Gonzaga University, in 1976, his mentor and good friend, then-head basketball coach Dan Fitzgerald, gave him life-impacting advice, telling him, “You’ve got to do three things in life, Tony: give back to your school, give back to your community and give back to your profession.”

So began a lifetime commitment to help his community, by volunteering with a variety of local community organizations. He started the still-in-existence Bulldog Club, where he served as president, as well as serving on various boards and foundations, including Central Valley School District Boards and Fundraising Committees, Gonzaga University Dean’s Business Forum Advisory Board, the Foundation Board of Community Colleges of Spokane, the Inland Northwest Planned Giving Council, and Associated Industries Board of Directors.

Whether it is through his professional endeavors or volunteer experiences, Higley’s passion is giving back to the community that has given so much to him.

profileData.profile_description: default agent role for Brandon Marchand - Spokane Home Guy
profileData.title: Broker/Owner
profileData.bio: The original Spokane Home Guy Brandon Marchand started as a solo agent in 2007. As he gained momentum, creating a name for himself in the Spokane area Brandon created a vision for a team that became The Spokane Home Guy Group. Along the way he collected exceptional talent by partnering with other high producing agents, administrative staff, and reliable business partners. Today, SHG is over 20 agents strong with two expansion groups servicing the greater Spokane area, North Idaho and Central Washington. The team has been ranked in the top 20% for Spokane area realtors since 2007, placed in The Wall Street Journal's "The Thousand" group of top real estate agents in America, and sold over 320 homes in 2019. More importantly, the group has had the privilege of partnering with several local organizations to give back in the community in which they live and serve. The Spokane Home Guy Group continues to grow and takes pride in establishing relationships that empower people to win.
specialties: Spokane and Coeur d'Alene Real Estate

profileData.profile_description: default agent role for Desiree Renshaw
profileData.title: Agent
profileData.bio:
My name is Desiree Renshaw, and I am a licensed Real Estate agent serving buyers, sellers, and investors in the Spokane area. I chose this line of work because I love connecting with people. Building relationships and helping others achieve their goals is fulfillment of a lifelong dream for me.  I understand that buying or selling a home is both logical and emotional. As your guide, I do everything possible to facilitate a smooth transaction and produce win-win results. It doesn’t matter whether you’re a first-time buyer, moving up or investing, I approach every new opportunity with the same attention, patience, and intuition to ensure a positive experience.  A referral is the greatest compliment you can give me—one that helps me build my community and reach more people.

Born and raised in Salt Lake City, Utah, I’ve always been a people person at heart! My diverse background includes Dutch and Indonesian ancestry. I am lucky enough to have three siblings—one biological and two adopted from Korea. My college years were spent in Idaho, earning a BS in Psychology from Boise State University. After completing my degree, I gained valuable experience in customer service and spent time volunteering for Big Brothers and Sisters, the Special Olympics, and the Agency for New Americans.  I made many connections in the Treasure Valley and met my husband, Ryan, there too. His job relocation in 2008 brought us to Spokane, WA.  Since moving here, we’ve had the great fortune to experience and grow to love all that this area has to offer a young family: proximity to nature, reasonable cost of living, and the wonderful residents who also proudly call this place home!

Ryan and I are proud parents of two young sons, and we share our home with a wonderful yellow lab named Ella. When I’m not working, I spend time hiking, cycling, golfing, and doing yoga. I also love running through neighborhood parks, gardening, and reading.  I belong to two book clubs and love hosting friends and family in my cozy home.

I can’t wait to meet you and talk about your goals. And I welcome the opportunity to work hard on your behalf to turn your real estate dreams to reality.

feedbackData.comment:
5 Stars is not a high enough rating!!! 
Kristi represented me as a seller’s agent, and I can’t begin say enough good things about her.  Kristi is extremely personable and great to work with.  She returned every call or text quickly, patiently answered every dumb question, and was right there at every step.  Where she really shined was in her knowledge of the market, as well as her organization and presentation. She truly made the process of selling a house painless. 
 
During our initial meeting and walk-through, she quickly identified a number of things that needed to be done to sell the house, as well as recommending some things that could be done to set the house apart from others in its class.  Within a few days of that meeting, she had a very thorough and detailed market analysis completed.  
 
In tune with rapidly changing market conditions during the 3 months between market analysis and putting the house on the market, Kristi’s diligence and expertise allowed us to list the house 17% above market analysis, and we received 6 full price and above offers in just 5 days.  She was a great sport and fun to work with, conducting a 2 day open house in conjunction with an estate sale.  
 
Kristi kindly and patiently helped me review offers and helped identify the right buyer, one that offered $15,000 above asking price, with the ability to close in less than 30 days.  The sale was completed without a hitch at 22% above initial market analysis, totally due to Kristi’s expertise and hard work.

profileData.profile_description: default agent role for Danielle LaBar
profileData.title: Broker
profileData.bio: I am happy to be helping buyers and sellers in my hometown of Cheney, WA and the surrounding Spokane area! I began my real estate career in 2005 when I moved to Manhattan while attending Baruch University. After a couple more moves (South Carolina and then Seattle) I decided to settle down in Cheney to be close to my siblings, parents, and friends and finish my marketing degree at EWU. Real Estate transactions can be rather stressful and cumbersome for buyers and sellers so my goal is to relieve the stress and help my clients obtain their goals with at much ease as possible. I pride myself on the first class service that I provide to each and every client that I work with. When listing a property I handle everything from professional flyers and marketing materials to maneuvering the appraisal process. Buyers receive utmost support and help from the very beginning--answering questions about home buying to guidance through the loan process.  If you are looking at buying, selling, or just have questions regarding the real estate process please feel free to contact me!

profileData.profile_description: default agent for Jennifer Tiffany
profileData.bio:
Real Estate has been a part of my life since I was a child.  My parents worked in the industry and when I was in 9th grade I started working for their company after school and continued with them until a year after I graduated.

After having my children, I ventured back into the Real Estate industry as a Realtor in Coeur d'Alene, Idaho toward the end of the 1990's.  I later moved to Spokane and began working in the lending side of things as a lender/processor.  I was then recruited into the Title and Escrow side of things and enjoyed learning and working in that industry for many years.  

I  found my professional home with Haven Real Estate Group in 2016 as their Operations Manager and have since become a licensed Real Estate Broker in the state of Washington.  My previous experience has served me well in this position and in the wonderful environment provided I have grown in experience and expertise both professionally and personally.

I have lived in a lot of places during my lifetime, but came to the Pacific Northwest in 1983 and fell in love with the beauty and all that it has to offer.  I love the outdoors and very much enjoy the mountains, rivers and lakes.  

I have 4 amazing children and am now blessed to be a grandma, which has been the most wonderful experience

profileData.profile_description: default agent role for Randy Wells
profileData.title: Broker
profileData.bio:
My goal in real estate is to take such great care of my clients that they refer everyone they know to me. It is that simple.

I have been working in the real estate business serving clients in the Spokane area for over 25 years. I work with my mom from time to time, who has been selling real estate for over 45 years, and we have an assistant that keeps us organized and on track. I primarily specialize in residential real estate, from high-end properties to first-time home buyers, as well as luxury homes and investment and rental income properties. I’ve also helped many clients over the years with relocating to the beautiful Inland Northwest area that we call home. Over 95% of my business is from repeat clients and referrals from those clients. My goal is simple, make sure my buyers and sellers are happy now, 6 months from now, and 6 years from now.

profileData.profile_description: default agent role for Jack Kestell
profileData.title: Broker/Owner
profileData.bio: Monte J. ™Jack™ Kestell Jr.Raised in Spokane Jack attended Our Lady of Fatima elementary, Gonzaga Prep and graduated from Ferris High School in 1973. Jack obtained his Real Estate Salesperson™s license within 2 weeks of his 18th birthday, and his Brokers license in 1977.Mr. Kestell™s Real Estate training, however, began when he was a child growing up going with his dad to the office on Saturdays. Jack™s Dad™s Real Estate Career began in the 1940™s and he retired in the early 1980™s. In 1981 Jack purchased Kestell Co.Over the past 35+ years he has been involved in nearly every aspect of the Real Estate Industry including:Listing and sales of new and resale homesListing and sales of raw land and lotsListing and sales of multi family / investment PropertiesListing and sales of Commercial PropertiesCommercial LeasingDevelopment of Single Family SubdivisionsMarketing New home CommunitiesZone Changes / Consulting / Land Use PlanningDevelopment of Commercial / Office BuildingsAcquisitionsConsultingMr. Kestell™s business philosophy is to treat every client and every transaction as if he were dealing on his own behalf, giving his best effort at all times.Jack holds membership in:National Association of RealtorsWashington State Association of RealtorsSpokane Association of RealtorsSpokane Multiple Listing ServiceNational Association of HomebuildersIndependent Brokers AssociationNotable Accomplishments:Assisted Condron Homes on the acquisition of 110 acres in NE Spokane that was developed into a 455 lot subdivision. The ™Bluegrass™ development was marketed by Kestell Co. and sold out over an approximate 10 year period resulting in over $70,000,000 in sales.Assisted in the acquisition of 70 acres on Day Mt Spokane Rd that was developed into a 120 lot subdivision. The ™Brighton Place™ development was marketed by Kestell Co. and sold out over an approximate 8 year period resulting in over $21,000,000 in sales.Development and partnership management of a 22,000 square foot medical / dental professional office building. Mr. Kestell managed construction of the ™2700 Southeast Blvd™ and has been responsible for preparation of leases and ongoing management of the facility.Zone change of 100,000 Square feet of land at ™57th and Palouse Hwy™ from low density residential to Community Commercial.Assisted in the Acquisition of 60 acres on the West Plains. The ™Sekani at Crosspointe™ development consists of 250 lots for single family homes. The project is 50% complete. Kestell Co. has been involved since acquisition and is responsible for marketing of the project.Involved in the development of the ™Highland Estates™ project in the Spokane Valley. Kestell Co. has been marketing the project which is expected to exceed 500 units. To date approximately 200 homes exist in the neighborhood.Since the early 1990™s, Mr. Kestell has consistently been one of the TOP 15 SALES VOLUME PRODUCERS within the Spokane Multiple Listing Service.

profileData.title: Broker
profileData.bio:
My Story
I purchased my first home right out of college and I’ve been passionate about Real Estate ever since.
I’m here to serve you in a way that truly meets your needs.  I don’t view your real estate goals as transactions, I believe we can add value to each other’s lives and communities for a life a time.
If you’re looking to have a successful home sale that generates you the most money in your pocket, empowers you to spend time on the lifestyle you want to live and inspires you to make your next real estate purchase, you’re looking in the right place.
I focus on leading my clients to get the results they want, whatever that may be.  If they are curious about the value of their home or considering a move, I’m there. 
When their kid graduates from college and is ready to purchase their first home, I’m there.
When they find out they’re expecting a baby and decide to purchase their first investment property, I’m there.  
No matter the reason, when they call, I’m there.
When I’m away from business, you can catch me outside feeding my soul with my family/friends; hiking, biking, backpacking, fishing or just enjoying the sun.
My Mission – 
Empower clients to fearlessly reach their real estate goals
My Core Values – 
Embrace the joy in life
Be ambitious, consistent and create opportunity 
Take care of ourselves, others and our community
Seek empathy and compassion for others
Always keep growing

profileData.profile_description: default agent for Gavin Hale
profileData.bio:
Hi, my name is Gavin Hale, I was born and raised in the beautiful Spokane area. I believe that your home is your sanctuary and should be treated as such. Whether you’re buying your first home, looking to invest in property or seeking that dream residence, the experience should be nothing less than seamless. I understand that your home is more than just a place to live — it’s where you make long-lasting memories.

Before real estate, I worked customer service as well as landscape and construction. My experience in customer service showed me how to be genuine with others and treat everyone with respect and dignity, always put your client’s best interest first, and helped me learn my true passion for helping others. My experience with landscape and construction taught me how to work hard until everything is complete, give my all no matter what, and get my hands dirty when need be.

I help my clients navigate the often-challenging waters of the home buying and selling process, with the end result only being a wonderful and fun experience. When I’m not busy helping clients, I enjoy spending time with my other half and our two cats, as well as our family and friends. I also enjoy playing basketball, meeting new people and helping others in any way that I can. I'm a family man, so I understand putting you and your family’s best interest as the number one priority. I will do everything in my power to help you and your families achieve whatever it is you're striving for. I look forward to hearing from you.

profileData.profile_description: default agent for Parker Spradling
profileData.bio:
Parker Spradling grew up in the Spokane region, which makes him a natural choice to talk to clients who are considering moving to the area and considering its value to their family. As a local, he knows the natural beauty of the area and is a testament to the great educational opportunities that abound throughout the region. In fact, Parker was quite involved in a variety of leadership groups throughout high school such as Leadership Spokane and the National Student Leadership Conference all of which prepared him well for his future working as a real estate agent.

While he is obviously a born leader, one thing that all of his clients recognize is his dedication to them and his great communication skills. Parker's goal throughout any transaction is to act as an ally who will always go the extra mile to make sure that each and every client finds their dream home. In fact, it is not uncommon to find Parker after hours chatting with a client and just shooting the breeze, because he is generally invested in each and every client who comes into his door. He is well aware that buying or selling a home is the largest undertaking most people will take, and gives the decision to buy or sell his full attention and respect.

profileData.profile_description: default agent for Marc Henning
profileData.title: Agent
profileData.bio:
The first mission of Mint Realty is simple – to provide consistent, top-notch customer service to every single client. This is accomplished by establishing a relationship with my clients, listening to their plans and goals, and then putting a plan together to make it all happen. For sellers – my attention to detail and desire to present homes and properties at a high level has proven to be highly successful in separating them from the rest of the pack. I’m there to guide you along the way and help make it as easy as possible. For Buyers – it simply comes down to listening and understanding what you want, knowing the area and market well, and then being able to get that perfect property when it does become available. I think you’ll find I’m easy to talk with, completely trustworthy, and am fully committed, resulting in your success.

The second part of my mission is to offer value and support to the community. I grew up in the Spokane area and want to see every person, school, and local business flourish. I love to support our local charities and businesses, sponsor school activities, and contribute in whatever way I can to the area.

The Spokane area is home to me. My wife Molly and I have 4 amazing kids between the ages of 9 and 15.

Create a Comparative Market Analysis for your house

Assist you in setting a marketable price

Explain how to prepare your house for sale

Qualify buyers for your house and review contract offers

Allow you to cancel your listing at any time with no penalty under our Easy Exit Listing Agreement

As your Buyer's Specialists we at The Legacy Group will:

Put your interests first and foremost

Develop a comprehensive understanding of your wants and needs in a new home

Value your time and show you homes that fit your criteria and fall within your price range

Clearly communicate current market conditions and trends

Negotiate terms and the structure of the contract on your behalf

Work toward a satisfying and efficient closing for all concerned

profileData.slogan: Not you average Real Estate Company
profileData.bio:
PNW Properties is not the average real estate company. Our Brokers are consultants, educators and professionals who share in the company’s mission to help each of our clients, either buyers or sellers, make the most educated decision regarding their real estate transaction. Our focus is to ensure that our clients have all of the unbiased information to make smart decisions and make the move of their dreams as stress free as possible. We specialize in first time home buyers, but have the expertise and experience to assist all stages of buyers and sellers.

PNW Properties was created by a husband and wife broker team that started in the real estate industry in 2007.  Annette was the first to become a licensed broker and Shawn followed, after his career as an EMT and Fire Fighter forced him into early retirement. They both were born and raised in Spokane and Spokane Valley and raised their own family here. They have very strong ties to this community. Together they provide exceptional service to their clients by walking them through every step of the process. They share their knowledge and explain each step. They believe in helping their clients understand what they are signing and how it will affect them. They are not in the business of selling real estate, they are in the business of building lifelong relationships.

profileData.title: Agent
profileData.slogan: Kevin Your Spokane and CDA area Realtor
profileData.bio:
Kevin Scherer is a real estate agent in the Coeur d’Alene Idaho and Spokane WA areas serving Post Falls, Hayden, Dalton Gardens, Rathdrum, Athol and the entire Coeur d’Alene Lake area as well as Spokane, Mead, Greenbluff, Colbert, Green Acres, Otis Orchards, Liberty Lake, and Spokane Valley.  Kevin has 30 years of real estate experience in several different aspects of real estate from investing, property management, property development and custom construction. 

Prior to becoming an agent Kevin sold his families 1st home at the ripe young age of 12yrs old!  After that they built a new custom home every 4-6 years.  Kevin went on to college at Washington State University graduating with a B.S. in Environmental Studies.  Upon graduation he moved to the Portland/Vancouver area and started a Environmental Consulting and contracting business.  The business was involved in over 1000 residential and commercial real estate transactions over the next 10 years of business.  During that time Kevin also started investing in real estate and developing property while raising 2 kids and working on his own dream property.  With investing (buying and selling) in real estate Kevin was involved in approximately 50 purchase and sale agreements prior to ever becoming a licensed real estate agent.
  
In 2007 Kevin took a position with the Idaho Transportation Department as their Environmental Planner and moved his family back to the Spokane/CDA area.  In 2016 Kevin decided to take his 30 years of experience in real estate and do what he loves the most, which is helping people.  Kevin’s goal is to take what he knows about being on both sides of a real estate deal and give his clients the best experience possible and help his clients reach their own goals and dreams in purchasing or selling real estate.

Upon meeting Mr. Baker it is apparent that he cares about finding you the perfect home. The first day of looking at houses, he gave me different tips about what to look for in a home such as new windows, gas heating, the overall condition of the neighborhood to name a few. This may seem like obvious advice to some, but for a first time home buyer, it was invaluable. I came away from that first experience grateful that I had someone knowledgeable about the area and surprised by how easy it had been. I couldn't imagine working with anyone else. 
Once we found what I believed to be the perfect home, Mr. Baker went above and beyond helping me set up both a sewer and home inspection that he recommended. I was extremely satisfied with the quality of both. The inspections were thorough and not biased in any way to influence me to continue with the sale or move on. The honesty and quality of the inspections led me to remove my offer on the first home.
We kept looking, Mr. Baker meanwhile accommodating my busy schedule that included me being out of contact for 5 days, until we finally found an even better house than the first. He and I discussed a good offer that was comfortable with my budget which came in at just under 97 percent of the asking price. The sellers accepted the offer. When it came time to assess the inspection report and make a list of what we would like fixed, the list we made with was reasonable for both me and the seller and ended up being agreeable to both sides. 
Finally the final walk-through and closing day came around and Mr. Baker was diligent in making sure that everything was to my liking and that I understood everything I was signing. When I got the keys, he was genuinely happy for me and made it clear that I could give him a call if I had any questions about anything. 
Overall, Mr. Baker is above and beyond what I could have asked for in a realtor. There are people who care about the final bottom line and there are those who care about the people they work for and doing their absolute best in all things. Mr. Baker is the latter. He is honest, hardworking, respectful, easy to talk to, and a delight to work with. I know that when I eventually buy another home, Mr Baker has set the bar high in what I expect from a realtor. If you are looking for a realtor, John Baker is the one to choose.
John was there to help every step of the way for me, a first time home buyer. And I will be recommencing him to my future home-buying friends.

I have been a licensed Real Estate Agent in Washington for 30 years and recently obtained my Associated Broker License in Idaho.  I have lived in the Spokane area my entire life so I very familiar with the area.

These are things I do for my clients.  I treat them as I would want to be treated.  

I am here to open new doors for you and go that extra mile.

profileData.bio:
Meet Mindy Jo Lyons, the REALTOR® who embodies integrity, energy, hard work, and creative service in every aspect of your transaction. With Mindy Jo, you're not just getting a REALTOR®, you're getting a trusted partner who will go the extra mile to make your real estate dreams a reality.

Born and raised in the greater Spokane area, Mindy Jo knows the local market like the back of her hand. Having moved a whopping 17 times in the area with her husband and family, she has gained unparalleled experience in buying and selling residential properties in South Hill, Elk, Deer Park, Chattaroy, Mead, West Plains, and Nine Mile Falls just to name a few. She works in Spokane, Stevens, Pend Oreille & Lincoln Counties and is happy to help you wherever you need to sell or purchase.

When she's not busy making her clients' dreams come true, Mindy Jo enjoys fishing, lake life, and cheering on her kids in their sports activities. She is also very active at the national, state, and local levels of real estate education & leadership. She is committed to staying ahead of the game, she strives to keep up-to-date with the latest market trends, laws, and products to best serve her clients' needs.

Specializing in all aspects of buying, selling, and more, Mindy Jo is passionate about helping her clients achieve their real estate goals. So whether you're a first-time buyer and/or seller or a seasoned investor, you can trust Mindy Jo to guide you through every step of the process with enthusiasm, expertise, and a smile on her face. Get in touch today and let Mindy Jo help you with all your real estate goals!

profileData.profile_description: default agent for Ken Jones

office.name: CENTURY 21 Beutler & Associates
office.slogan: Global reach, local knowledge

profileData.bio:
Ken is a Spokane native that attended North Central High School. Currently Ken resides in Liberty Lake and has been a member of this community since September of 2020. As a member of CENTURY 21 Beutler & Associates, Ken assists both buyers and sellers with residential real estate in Spokane, Liberty Lake, and the surrounding areas.

Prior to Real Estate, Ken had served in the United States Navy and most recently worked as a Budget & Financial Analyst for the Community Colleges of Spokane, a Budget Analyst & Fiscal Specialist for Eastern Washington University, and in Financial Development for the YMCA & Camp Reed. Ken Graduated from Eastern Washington University with a Bachelor Degree in Business with a major in Management of Information Systems where he learned how to build databases and manipulate data. Ken uses his knowledge of databases, as well as, his past experiences as an analyst to support/assist his home buyers and sellers in the community with real estate decisions based on the analytics of the data at hand.
Ken primarily joined real estate because: “My wife has been a REALTOR for several years now  for a major developer, and watching how fulfilled she is has inspired me to do the same. The joy you get to see from families being able to get into their new home or helping them sell their home to start the next season in their life is priceless." If not assisting clients, you will probably find Ken spending time with family & friends, reading, playing hockey, golfing, or snowboarding.

“My business model hinges around customer service. I strive to be available for my clients with open communication making sure that they are always in the know. I am committed to honesty, integrity, trust, and respect in every transaction with my clients.”

I am originally from the west side of Washington State but have called the eastern half "HOME" ever since I stepped foot on the WSU campus in '97. If you are looking for a "Full Service" Realtor, whether you are ready now or a year from now, please give me call and let me know how I can help.

profileData.profile_description: default agent for Travis Lawrence
profileData.bio:
A longtime Washington State resident, Travis Lawrence brings more than two decades of sales and service experience and a reputation for honesty, reliability, and superior negotiating skills to his role as REALTOR® with Realty ONE Group Eclipse.

Originally from Western Washington, Travis moved to Spokane in 2018 to be closer to family and provide a better education for his children. This cross-state leap led Travis to realize the value of home ownership after a decade of renting and fueled his dream to apply his decades-long hospitality experience into the exciting world of real estate.

Patient, candid, and committed to his clients’ success, Travis joined Realty ONE Group Eclipse for their experience and support. With their integrated marketing strategies and tools, Travis can market your home to a vast demographic of home buyers, getting your home sold as fast as possible. Travis treats each client as if they are a member of his own family, negotiating on behalf of their best interests, taking the stress and guess work away, and assuring satisfaction.

A proud father to his three-year-old daughter and two stepchildren, when Travis is not holding an open house or searching for the perfect property for a client, he enjoys kayaking at the lake in the spring, softball and BBQs in the summer, biking the Centennial Trail in the fall, and sledding and snowboarding at Mt. Spokane in the winter.

If you are looking to buy your dream home or sell the one you have, you owe it to yourself to give me a call. I proudly serve Eastern Washington with a special focus on Spokane, Spokane Valley, and the surrounding areas.

I am well known for my innovation, enthusiasm, and client-centric approach to business. I bring the small town values I learned growing up in Stevensville, MT to the often impersonal world of real estate. I have a passion for helping first time home buyers and love to be your ultimate advocate. I love guiding clients through the home buying process and helping them overcome any obstacles that appear in their path.

Buying or selling a home is always easier when you have an advocate in your corner. I keep my focus squarely on you and your needs at all times. I am always researching new marketing techniques and trends to ensure you are being served by the absolute best in the industry. And when it comes to communication I have a saying: “Communicate before a follow up is requested.” You will always be well informed every stage of the transaction!

I helps my clients see the possibilities in every opportunity. Quite often there is hidden value in a property that a professional like me will help you uncover. This may require some flexible thinking, but I will ensure you understand the pros and cons of every facet of a potential deal. I will give you the honest counsel you need when you need it most.

When I’m not scouring the MLS for your next home, I like to get outdoors and enjoy time on the lake paddle-boarding or with her my crazy cocker spaniel, Cooper. I love to try new restaurants (hole in the walls are the best!) and if you need a new TV show to binge, I’ve got you covered!

profileData.bio:
Hi!

My name is Curtis Miller. 

I grew up in Western Pennsylvania and graduated from Tech Memorial High School in 1965, majoring in business. Immediately after high school, I joined the US Navy and served in Vietnam from 1965-1968. I served with honor on the The USS ENTERPRISE CVN-65. I then was blessed with a 33-year career with Northwest Airlines at the Chicago O’Hare, Milwaukee airport and Spokane International Airport as a Customer Service and Supervising Manager. I began my Real Estate career in 2004, and have enjoyed a successful career to the present day!

My Client-First Philosophy

There are many qualities and skills necessary for excellence as a real estate professional. They include integrity, in-depth community and market knowledge, marketing savvy, effective negotiation skills and a high-quality, professional network -- all of which are hallmarks of how I work.

In my experience as a Spokane real estate professional, I've found that providing the very best service is essentially about putting my clients first and responding quickly to client needs. To do so, demands accessibility as well as being both a good listener and a good communicator. 

This "client first" philosophy, which has always been my approach, requires that I continually improve my skills and find better ways of doing business -- including utilization of the latest technologies to do everything I've always done, only much more quickly and efficiently. They've also helped me to extend the range of services I can provide to my clients.

profileData.profile_description: default agent role for Veronica Johnson
profileData.title: Broker
profileData.slogan: Helping Folks Make Informed Real Estate Decisions
profileData.bio:
Veronica’s goal is to educate consumers on the current market climate and the fundamentals of how the purchase and sale of real estate works, so they can make an informed decision on what is best for them and in their best interest.

With a passion for helping others, her focus is on quality, not quantity.  Veronica is committed to providing an exceptional real estate experience by facilitating an enjoyable, smooth, and as stress-free as possible home buying and/or selling journey, ensuring a quality transaction – every time!

Veronica has been a full-time licensed REALTOR® since 2014.  Her success is based on more than 80% referrals and repeat business from satisfied clients.  Veronica’s clientele appreciates her low-pressure sales approach, patience, knowledge, negotiation skills, the ability to properly price and market real estate, and her knack to listen to and observe what they want and are looking for in a home.


3 Things Veronica does with and for her clients:
1.  Consult with you…She will make sure you are able to make an educated and informed decision every step of the way.

2.  Negotiate for you…She will treat your transaction like it is her personal transaction.

3.  Handle all the details for you…She will make sure the numerous steps in the real estate transaction are managed properly in a timely manner and communicate with ALL parties involved in the purchase/sale of your home.


3 Pledges to her clients:
1.  She will promptly respond and stay in regular contact.

2. She will do what she says she is going to do.

3. She will be brutally honest.


Get to Know Veronica
As a resident of Spokane for more than 20 years, Veronica has an in-depth knowledge of the Greater Spokane area and the real estate market.  She has lived and worked in many places including; Alaska, California, Illinois, Indiana, Montana, Nevada, and Washington State.  She knows what it is like to make long-distance relocations and learn about new areas.

In her free time, you can find Veronica maintaining her flowerbeds and yard, playing with her dog Milo, and always learning something new, whether it is improving herself to better serve her clients, new real estate trends, marketing concepts, or history on just about any topic.

Professional Philosophy
“Do the right thing.”  Your experience is Stephanie’s top priority!  She provides the highest level of service, professionalism, and enjoyment to everyone she engages with.  Purchasing real estate, a major investment, is one of the most complicated decisions a person will make.   It should also be one of the most fun and exciting.  Stephanie’s goal is to ensure your real estate purchase is exceptionally positive from start to finish.  She wants to earn your trust and those of your family and friends for a life time!

Background
Stephanie is a results-driven individual with 15 years of leadership and marketing experience at Huppin’s HiFi Photo& Video / OneCall. profileData.bio: Mae grew up in Hunters, WA. After graduating high school, she obtained her EMT certification and cross-trained as a Firefighter working for the Spokane Tribe of Indians. She then graduated from nursing school at Spokane Community College with her RN and graduated from Lewis and Clark State College with her BSN. She started working at Sacred Heart Children's Hospital. After 12 years in the medical industry, her entrepreneurial spirit led her to a career in Real Estate. In her spare time, Mae enjoys spending time with her 2 children. She enjoys riding bikes on the centennial trails, hiking around Dishman Hills, fishing at Newman Lake, and camping in Colville. She volunteers at various places in Spokane Valley working with rescue dogs. She chose Century 21 because she wanted to work for a company that believes in supporting each other and providing essential resources and training to help her better serve her clients. If you want help finding a house or selling the one you have, contact Mae at 509-703-9314 . She would love to help you on your journey!

profileData.bio:
Leadership, Contributions & Recognition:

• Washington REALTOR® since 1989
• Past President Lewis County Association of REALTORS® -1998
• Past President Spokane Association of REALTORS® -2008
• Selected as one of seven Washington realtors to attend and graduate from Leadership Institute Northwest-2006
• Served on State and Local Committees for Education, Business Practices, Government Affairs, Professional Standards, Communications, Technology, Budget & Finance, Nominations and Special Events Fundraising
• Spokane Representative for Washington REALTORS® Statewide Forms Committee
• Eastern Washington Regional Representative-Washington REALTORS® Executive Committee
• Mentor/Trainer for Windermere realtors
• Award winning top Real Estate Teams in Spokane specializing in South Hill and greater Spokane area of Premier Properties
• "VOTED 2009 SPOKANE REALTOR® OF THE YEAR.

"Why am I a Realtor?"

I take pride in raising the level of professionalism from years of involvement with Washington REALTORS® and the Spokane Association of REALTORS®. My clients depend on my education, expertise and professionalism to assist them with important decisions regarding their home investments. By staying on top of our changing market and industry, I am able to provide the best strategies for negotiations and marketing advice for my clients. I truly enjoy and find great satisfaction in knowing that I am the trusted advisor in helping Buyers and Sellers complete their successful journey with their home experience. As a realtor, I am a member of the National Association of REALTORS® and held to the high standards of a strict Code of Ethics.

Family and Community,  friends, faith and community are very important in my life. Balance is critical and with our busy lifestyles and culture, it can be challenging to create personal time. My husband, Jerry and I are recognized as "The Boyd Team" and offer over 50 years of combined Real Estate experience to our clients. Jerry is also licensed in Arizona. We enjoy golf, outdoor activities and relaxation at many beautiful area lakes and mountains.

We are members of Manito Country Club and The Spokane Club. We support the Mark Rypien Children's Foundation, Meals on Wheels, Boys and Girls Club, Habitat for Humanity, Spokane Guild School and many other charitable organizations. Spokane offers great shopping from "tucked away" boutiques to downtown Riverpark Square to Northtown and Valley malls. "Organic" and "Green Environment" is encouraged but not over-emphasized. Arts, entertainment and sports are diverse and very enjoyable.Living in SpokaneI moved to Spokane from Western Washington in 2000 and I see this community from a new and different perspective in understanding a Buyers first impression of Spokane and the questions that they commonly ask. I have watched this beautiful city grow in many directions and have been very impressed with the strong support of our schools, community, economic development and environment. This is a wonderful city to raise a family, be an entrepreneur, retire or just call home. Spokane has consistently rated as one of the top cities in the nation to live, work and play. I am proud of Spokane and how it continues to evolve and I look forward to helping you call Spokane your "Home" too.

broker.name: Washington State Land for Sale, LLC

profileData.title: Designated Managing Broker
profileData.slogan: Selling the finest land in Washington State
profileData.bio:
Americans hold the highest percentage of their wealth in real estate, so the decision to buy or sell land is often a life-changing event. Jesse considers the responsibility to uphold the highest ethics in these transactions to be sacred. A young farmer deciding to buy his own land for the first time or an investor divesting their ranch after generations of stewardship can be an overwhelming proposition that Jesse understands intimately. Personal relationships and ethical dealings have long been the cornerstones of Jesse's ambitions as a land broker and make her a vital asset to principals buying or selling land.

Jesse's land career started in rural California during the 2006 Recession when real estate prices were falling faster than foreclosure signs were going up. Her early years with an independent firm taught her ingenuity and determination which helped her become one of the top-selling land agents of the region. Learning to use and perfecting social media to promote properties and services, Jesse caught the attention of the Small Business Development Center and for a time Jesse contracted with economic development organizations to support entrepreneurship in rural communities.

Jesse's experience in land brokerage has been influenced by the nature of the geography she's lived in; she's not intimidated by dirt roads or mountain passes. In 2012 Jesse launched her own land brokerage in California specializing in recreational and agricultural properties. After 10 years, Jesse relocated with her husband and two children to the Pacific Northwest and decided to expand her brokerage services into Washington state.

Today, Jesse serves on the Executive Committee of the Washington Cattlemen’s Association, is a Washington State Farm Bureau Member, and Alumnus of Oregon State University’s College of Agricultural Science. The Ingels family are members of the Inland Northwest Wildlife Council and participate in habitat restoration projects, disabled hunter and fisherman access missions, and the annual Big Horn Sportsman’s Show. Jesse and her family can often be found camping, shooting, or rockhounding far beyond cell phone signal and electrical grids when they aren’t attending bull sales or farm tours.

profileData.profile_description: default agent for Sean Ness
profileData.title: Agent
profileData.bio:
Ever since he was a first-time home buyer, Sean has had a passion for all things real estate.  Each time he bought or sold a home, this passion only grew.  When he found himself scouring real estate listings in his spare time for family and friends whenever they were searching for a home, he knew it was time to make the jump into real estate fulltime!  Sean has been in the profession of helping people since graduating from Eastern Washington University in 2006.  First as a property adjuster with an insurance company here in Spokane and more recently managing customer support for a technology company based in Bellevue, WA.  Sean has been happily married to his high school sweetheart, Laura, for nearly 10 years.  They have two young and very active children together.  Sean enjoys spending summers on Lake Coeur d’Alene with his family and biking with his kids on the trails that run through Liberty Lake.  He’s an avid sports car enthusiast and enjoys attending cars & coffee meetups.  Sean’s also been rumored to play golf from time to time on the rare occasion some free time can be found. 
 
Both Sean and his wife are Spokane natives, having grown up not that far apart in the Spokane Valley.  Sean graduated from University High school in 2002, while his wife graduated from Central Valley High school.  After marriage, they purchased their first home together in Liberty Lake's River District neighborhood. They lived there until a job opportunity for Sean took them across the state to Seattle!  There, they purchased a 1950s mid-century modern home in Bellevue, WA.  They spent the next few years updating and remodeling the house while growing their family.  After 5 years of living and working in Bellevue, they decided it was time to return to the Spokane area.  They sold their house in Bellevue and purchased a home in Liberty Lake, where they currently reside.

profileData.bio:
Over 25 years ago, I bought my first house. The day I closed on it, I held those keys in my hand, and I was hooked on real estate!

After purchasing and selling over 20 properties-ranging from acreage, pre-owned homes, custom builds and investment homes-I decided that maybe this hobby should become my career. So, pairing my experience working in project management for a high-tech company, my ability to communicate and bring multiple parties together to negotiate and execute successful transactions, and my passion for real estate, I embarked upon my dream career. In 2008, I was awarded "Rookie of the Year," and in the decade since then, I have continued to work with hundreds of clients to expertly and successfully guide them through the sale and purchase of their homes. I find great satisfaction in helping clients find their perfect home, no matter how long it takes, and in providing essential information, clear communication and expert knowledge throughout the process. 

In addition to traditional real estate activity, I also enjoy helping clients through the intricacies of purchasing residential acreage and the process of building custom homes, barns and lakefront cabins. It is rewarding to help the clients I love find houses that will be a home, and for them, too, to hold those keys in their hands. Come work with me, it will be my greatest honor to be your Realtor of choice.

With over 9 years of experience as a realtor in the Spokane market, I gained a unique appreciation and perspective for individuals challenged by the 2008 housing crisis. Whether it’s helping people on the first steps of home ownership, facilitating the transition to your next home, or expanding your real estate portfolio, I want to be part of your journey.

My role as a trusted advisor is to educate my clients so they feel empowered in their decision making, during what can be an emotional process.  My experience, competency, drive, and tenacity all play a crucial part in my ability to ensure that my clients succeed in reaching their real estate goals. I work closely with my network of industry professionals, giving my clients access to a wealth of resources before, during, and after the transaction.

Born and raised in Spokane, I have watched it go from a sleepy town to a thriving city that has become one of the most desirable places to live in the nation. It takes no time at all for visitors to quickly realize the beauty and culture that Spokane has to offer. From the incredible four seasons of outdoor activities to our gorgeous neighborhood parks to a thriving downtown full of amazing shopping and restaurants, Spokane has it all.  These are just a few reasons why I love to call Spokane home.

profileData.title: Agent
profileData.bio:
I was born and raised in Seattle, Washington with the exception of a year in Brussels, Belgium at the age of 5 and 9 months in Oxford, England at the age of 12. I grew up spending summers in the San Juan Islands and upstate New York and spent A LOT of time looking at Open Houses with my Real Estate intrigued Parents. From this early exposure to homes came a love of all things Real Estate!
 
My career in Real Estate actually began with a move to Spokane in 2005 as the Relocation Manager for a Local Brokerage.  In this position I was the liaison between Real Estate Professionals and both Military and Corporate Buyers and Seller who were relocating in the Spokane area. Through this position I saw how exciting Real Estate could be, how much of a true advocate an excellent Realtor was for their clients and how much I enjoyed being a part of finding people move on to their next life goal!
  
In 2011 I began working as a full time Realtor, assisting both Buyer and Sellers achieve their next Real Estate Goal. I am committed to going above and beyond to make the entire Real Estate experience as enjoyable as possible for all parties involved while maintaining a reputation as a hardworking, ethical and fun Realtor! 

“I think it is extraordinarily important that as Realtors we remember that a home is the single largest investment most people will make in their lifetime. As a buyers agent my job is to help to guide them through a process in a way that allows them the most favorable (and least stressful) experience possible and make them thrilled to spend time in the home we assist them in buying. When it comes time to list their home it is important to recognize that this has been their home, and there are memories that come with the time spent in the home, and assist with helping them to move on to the next phase to the best of my ability. While this is a financial transaction, both as a buyer and a seller, it is also an emotional transaction. My single largest role in the transaction is to be my clients biggest advocate and champion, to listen to their wants and needs and then to work my absolute hardest to make those desires come true. I feel so honored each time people chose me to help them during this process.”

feedbackData.comment: Sarah is easy to communicate with, provided recommendations/advise based upon our needs, and was willing to 'go to bat' for us when it came to negotiations and keeping the process of buying our home moving forward.  I have already recommended Sarah to friends and family, and will continue to do so.

As a native of Spokane, I grew up enjoying all that the Inland Empire region continues to showcase including community activities, historical corner stones, and the abundance of surrounding natural beauty. Growing up I enjoyed many outdoor activities, ranging from camping, hiking, and boating at just a few of the many recreation areas that are just a short drive from town. Upon graduating from North Central high school, I ventured to Seattle to experience what the “big city” had to offer, and I absolutely fell in love with the eclectic way of life. I enjoyed as much of the culture, art, dim sum, and coffee that Seattle had to offer before I returned home to be closer to my family. After moving back, I focused on finishing my college degree.
I am a proud Whitworth graduate with a Bachelors in Humanities. Go Pirates! I was fortunate to have had the opportunity to learn from some of the great business professionals and leaders in Spokane’s community; they helped to foster my goals and guide me towards a career based around helping others. Through my search, I found my goals and passions aligned perfectly with a career in real estate. Jumping headfirst into this business was one of the best decisions I ever made. 
With a knack for creativity, I am passionate about finding innovative ways to turn the seemingly impossible tasks into an action plan for the end goal. 
I bring over 15 years of diverse outside experience to this role. As a result of this background, my approach is well-rounded, and I bring a high level of dedication and passion to my work. 
By day you can find me analyzing market data and market trends, cultivating new ways to grow my business, or attempting to perfect one of my social media posts. By night, you can find me enjoying a glass of wine while cuddling with my dog and pretending to be a Jeopardy whiz kid.
Wanna talk real estate? I would love to get to know you and your real estate goals! Reach out and let’s start your journey.

profileData.bio: Annie Franken is an energetic agent with a passion for the real estate industry. She is a Spokane native with strong family roots running throughout Washington. Her regional pride is abundantly clear by her keen interest in all things Northwest, especially it's more eccentric and quirky historical elements. Annie spent her early years making annual trips to Priest Lake, eventually taking a job working at the campgrounds where she developed relationships with tourists and locals alike. When she finished high school, Annie developed a wanderlust that took her across the globe. She spent years traveling from the sunny bays of Southern California, to the beautiful beaches on the North Shore of Oahu and the lush green mountains of Argentina. After years living amidst the hip cultural and art districts of Seattle and Portland, Annie returned to Spokane with fresh eyes for everything that makes the area such a wonderful and unique landscape. Today, as a real estate professional, she is applying her years of talent and skills in customer service to a dedicated career with Century 21. Annie's main priority is helping her clients by listening to their concerns and finding them a house that can be the home they've always wanted. She aims to make the process as fulfilling and rewarding as possible. Moving into a new home should be a comforting experience, not a stressful one. Annie dedicates herself to helping her clients each step of the way by providing a reliable, highly responsive, and trustworthy interaction. Whether it be the flexibility to adjust to changing circumstances, or a sense of humor when things aren't going as planned, she maintains the energy and drive needed to assure her clients are satisfied.

With over 20 years in community banking, I’ve helped hundreds of people buy or build their dream home and develop their investment properties. Through these transactions I’ve established reliable relationships with lenders, title companies, attorneys, accountants, inspectors and construction companies in our area. These relationships allow me to provide the best client experience available – with clear and realistic expectations, timely communication and the resources to solve problems should they arise.
Since establishing my family here in 1999, I’ve personally bought and sold numerous homes. The process can be emotional and challenging – and I love every minute of it! I look forward to sharing that feeling with you and appreciate the trust you put in me to handle your real estate needs.

profileData.profile_description: default agent for Joni Buyser
profileData.title: Broker
profileData.bio:
My desire to become a Realtor® started after purchasing my first home in 1992. The process intrigued me and the overall experience was rewarding. However, the dream of becoming a Realtor® was sidelined with the advent of my first child.  Life happened and with the addition of three more children and five major out of state moves my real estate career seemed to be perpetually put on hold. Those events, however, afforded me the opportunity to purchase seven houses and sell ten.  Each transaction was unique and exciting.

On several occasions, while relocating out of state, it was necessary to leave our home in the capable hands of a professional Realtor®. Having a dependable Realtor® with knowledge and expertise, someone who can handle every detail during the process, makes all the difference.

Relocating several times over the recent years has given me the real experience necessary to assist others through their process of finding and purchasing a home based on personal needs.

My passion for interior design allows me to help clients envision how properties could potentially be the home of their dreams, no matter the budget.

Since 1992, my goal as a Realtor® was and is to provide an exciting and rewarding real estate experience for those with whom I cross paths.

profileData.profile_description: default agent for Jesse Miller

team.name: Cambria Henry - Haven Real Estate Group WA

profileData.bio:
Serving and hard work are principles Spokane/North Idaho REALTOR® Jesse Miller has always lived by.

He grew up in the small town of Priest River in Northern Idaho and was raised to always put the community first. He quickly grew to recognize the accomplishment and self-fulfillment that comes from serving others.

Jesse discovered his love for real estate soon after starting the process of looking for his first home. He said that the process revealed a large-scale way to serve others that he could not pass up.

He soon started looking for a real estate agency to call home and stumbled across Haven Real Estate Group. After one meeting with Rob and Cambria, he knew it was the right place for him. He admired the agency’s dual focus on personal growth and cultivating exceptional client experiences.

Jesse is consistently a top-performing agent at Haven. Additionally, Jesse serves his peers in his role as a “Success Coach and Mentor.”

Often new agents struggle to figure out how to prioritize activities within their demanding schedule. Jesse walks them through the systems and tools available to agents and teaches them how to efficiently leverage those tools to serve their clients.

His hard work and determination allow Jesse to be the type of person that people immediately trust, and he believes this is what helps him excel for clients who need to sell or buy a home. Jesse believes that once you have the trust of a client they will be able to rely on you and that utter confidence will allow him to shoulder any stress or uncertainty for his clients.

In addition to building his career and mentoring agents, Jesse is also busy building his body. He competes in bodybuilding competitions, which he says have taught him the skills of determination and self-discipline which have spilled into his personal life. He explains that there are days when he doesn’t want to do the work, but he knows that he has to fight for his goals every day in order to succeed and he brings that same strong work ethic to his real estate clients.

profileData.bio:
I am Monte J Kestell III of Kestell Company Realtors located in Spokane, WA. Founded by my grandfather Monte Sr, Kestell Company Realtors has provided professional representation for buyers and sellers in residential and commercial real estate, new construction, investment properties, land development, rental income, recreational properties, and mobile home parks throughout Spokane and the inland empire for over 60 years. I have been an active licensed real estate broker for over 10 years. Not only do I have a tremendous amount of industry experience, but I am also dedicated and passionate about helping others in their journey of a successful sale or in locating an ideal property. 
	Selling your home is one of the most important financial decisions you can make. Normally one’s home is their most valuable asset. There are key components in devising a marketing strategy that will help insure that you receive the full financial potential available to you through the sale of your home or property. I would love to have the opportunity to sit down with you to present a marketing plan that I know will produce great results for you. Please feel free to contact me anytime. I would greatly appreciate the potential to assist you in any way possible and will go above and beyond expectation to fulfill your real estate needs.

To Buy Or Sell Call Monte Kestell

How I Can Help
I have been in real estate for over 30 years. 

As a former Master Home Builder, I built new homes for many years before becoming a Realtor. I am a Certified New Home Specialist, and am Residential Construction Certified. 

Why should that matter to you? Because understanding a house, how it is constructed, the land it sits on, and the neighboring properties, is key when considering the investment of purchasing your new home. 

If you are selling your home, I will offer my expert advice on which repairs you should make, what upgrades will pay off, and how to present your property in the best possible way. 

I provide to you a complete real estate service and am confident you will find in me a valuable asset for your real estate needs. 

Contact me and we'll see how I can be of assistance to you.

Dale Frazell

Jami, Aaron and their three children relocated many times over the years. They got to enjoy living in some pretty incredible places, including Hawaii and Alaska. Once retired from the Coast Guard, they decided to purchase a home in Spokane to be near family. Her two oldest children have gone on to start new adventures. Ethan joined the Air Force and Sydnie got married and is attending dental hygienist school.  Jami and Aaron are still blessed to have their youngest son, Aden, who is now in middle school at home with them.   

Jami wanted to use the knowledge acquired from running a home based business to help give clients excellent customer service and peace of mind in purchasing their new home.  She is committed to listening to her clients’ needs and her contacts and life experiences enable her to provide excellent customer service and peace of mind to her clients. 

As a full service real estate professional, Jami recognizes and values the trust clients place in her and strives every day to exceed their expectations. Clients appreciate her flexibility, low pressure sales, patience, and ability to listen and hear what her clients want. Jami is communicative, thorough, detail oriented and will be alongside you every step of the way.

profileData.bio: I’m the Managing Broker with Exit Real Estate North in Spokane, WA providing home-buyers and sellers with professional, responsive and attentive real estate services. Want an agent who'll really listen to what you want in a home? Need an agent who knows how to effectively market your home so it sells? Give me a call! I'm eager to help and would love to talk to you.

feedbackData.comment: If you are looking for an easy mannered, honest realestate agent who is both an expert in the field and who puts his clients needs first above sales, quotas and making commissions, then look no further than , Don Hatch. Trully his honest integrity is Unsurpassed! Whether buying and/or selling Don, sincerely cares about his clients individual needs, and sometimes daunting concerns when going through the process. Don will be with you and helping you the WHOLE way!!

I was sure we could not get the price for our home that Don set, but he made it happen.  The process was slowed by the sale of the buyers house in California, but Don kept us in the loop and explained everything.  It was a pleasure to use Don again for the sale of a home.

I have bought and sold homes with Don Hatches  great expertise.
Don is very reliable and knowledgeable when it comes to buying and selling homes.
He kept me in the loop at all times and made it his prioty to list my home in the best advertising market there is. As well as give me easy solutions to help sell my home that didn’t cost a lot of money or time.  #1  thing Don made it his job to sell my home so I didn’t have to make it my job. 
He also has a great team to back him up. Whom also make it their priority to take care of the buyer or seller.
Don has many connections with other realtors as well . That makes a huge difference for selling your home quicker.
He’s honest; fair and you can tell he loves what he does!
I highly recommend Don Hatch as your realtor! Hands down he’s the most efficient, professional,and reliable agent you’ll have.
